{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is called Hooked on a Feeling:"},{"time":2000,"text":"The Pursuit of Happiness and Human Design."},{"time":4000,"text":"I put up a somewhat dour Darwin,"},{"time":6000,"text":"but a very happy chimp up there."},{"time":8000,"text":"My first point is that the pursuit of happiness is obligatory."},{"time":11000,"text":"Man wishes to be happy, only wishes to be happy,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and cannot wish not to be so."},{"time":17000,"text":"We are wired to pursue happiness,"},{"time":19000,"text":"not only to enjoy it, but to want more and more of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"So given that that's true,"},{"time":24000,"text":"how good are we at increasing our happiness?"},{"time":28000,"text":"Well, we certainly try."},{"time":30000,"text":"If you look on the Amazon site, there are over 2,000 titles"},{"time":33000,"text":"with advice on the seven habits, the nine choices,"},{"time":36000,"text":"the 10 secrets,"},{"time":38000,"text":"the 14,000 thoughts that are supposed to bring happiness."},{"time":41000,"text":"Now another way we try to increase our happiness"},{"time":43000,"text":"is we medicate ourselves."},{"time":45000,"text":"And so there's over 120 million prescriptions out there for antidepressants."},{"time":49000,"text":"Prozac was really the first absolute blockbuster drug."},{"time":52000,"text":"It was clean, efficient, there was no high,"},{"time":55000,"text":"there was really no danger, it had no street value."},{"time":58000,"text":"In 1995,"},{"time":60000,"text":"illegal drugs were a $400 billion business,"},{"time":63000,"text":"representing eight percent of world trade,"},{"time":65000,"text":"roughly the same as gas and oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"These routes to happiness haven't really increased happiness very much."},{"time":71000,"text":"One problem that's happening now is,"},{"time":73000,"text":"although the rates of happiness"},{"time":75000,"text":"are about as flat as the surface of the moon,"},{"time":77000,"text":"depression and anxiety are rising."},{"time":79000,"text":"Some people say this is because we have better diagnosis,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and more people are being found out."},{"time":85000,"text":"It isn't just that. We're seeing it all over the world."},{"time":88000,"text":"In the United States right now"},{"time":90000,"text":"there are more suicides than homicides."},{"time":92000,"text":"There is a rash of suicide in China."},{"time":94000,"text":"And the World Health Organization predicts"},{"time":96000,"text":"by the year 2020"},{"time":98000,"text":"that depression will be"},{"time":100000,"text":"the second largest cause of disability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"Now the good news here"},{"time":104000,"text":"is that if you take surveys from around the world,"},{"time":106000,"text":"we see that about three quarters of people"},{"time":108000,"text":"will say they are at least pretty happy."},{"time":110000,"text":"But this does not follow any of the usual trends."},{"time":114000,"text":"For example, these two show great growth in income,"},{"time":117000,"text":"absolutely flat happiness curves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"My field, the field of psychology,"},{"time":122000,"text":"hasn't done a whole lot"},{"time":124000,"text":"to help us move forward in understanding human happiness."},{"time":127000,"text":"In part, we have the legacy of Freud, who was a pessimist,"},{"time":130000,"text":"who said that pursuit of happiness is a doomed quest,"},{"time":132000,"text":"is propelled by infantile aspects of the individual"},{"time":136000,"text":"that can never be met in reality."},{"time":138000,"text":"He said, \"One feels inclined to say"},{"time":141000,"text":"that the intention that man should be happy"},{"time":143000,"text":"is not included in the plan of creation.\""},{"time":146000,"text":"So the ultimate goal of psychoanalytic psychotherapy"},{"time":149000,"text":"was really what Freud called ordinary misery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"And Freud in part reflects"},{"time":157000,"text":"the anatomy of the human emotion system --"},{"time":160000,"text":"which is that we have both a positive and a negative system,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and our negative system"},{"time":166000,"text":"is extremely sensitive."},{"time":168000,"text":"So for example, we're born loving the taste of something sweet"},{"time":171000,"text":"and reacting aversively to the taste of something bitter."},{"time":175000,"text":"We also find that people are more averse to losing"},{"time":178000,"text":"than they are happy to gain."},{"time":181000,"text":"The formula for a happy marriage"},{"time":183000,"text":"is five positive remarks, or interactions,"},{"time":186000,"text":"for every one negative."},{"time":188000,"text":"And that's how powerful the one negative is."},{"time":191000,"text":"Especially expressions of contempt or disgust,"},{"time":194000,"text":"well you really need a lot of positives to upset that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"I also put in here the stress response."},{"time":201000,"text":"We're wired for dangers that are immediate,"},{"time":203000,"text":"that are physical, that are imminent,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and so our body goes into an incredible reaction"},{"time":208000,"text":"where endogenous opioids come in."},{"time":210000,"text":"We have a system that is really ancient,"},{"time":212000,"text":"and really there for physical danger."},{"time":214000,"text":"And so over time, this becomes a stress response,"},{"time":217000,"text":"which has enormous effects on the body."},{"time":219000,"text":"Cortisol floods the brain;"},{"time":221000,"text":"it destroys hippocampal cells and memory,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and can lead to all kinds of health problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"But unfortunately, we need this system in part."},{"time":229000,"text":"If we were only governed by pleasure"},{"time":231000,"text":"we would not survive."},{"time":233000,"text":"We really have two command posts."},{"time":235000,"text":"Emotions are short-lived intense responses"},{"time":237000,"text":"to challenge and to opportunity."},{"time":240000,"text":"And each one of them allows us to click into alternate selves"},{"time":243000,"text":"that tune in, turn on, drop out"},{"time":245000,"text":"thoughts, perceptions, feelings and memories."},{"time":248000,"text":"We tend to think of emotions as just feelings."},{"time":250000,"text":"But in fact, emotions are an all-systems alert"},{"time":252000,"text":"that change what we remember,"},{"time":254000,"text":"what kind of decisions we make,"},{"time":256000,"text":"and how we perceive things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So let me go forward to the new science of happiness."},{"time":260000,"text":"We've come away from the Freudian gloom,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and people are now actively studying this."},{"time":265000,"text":"And one of the key points in the science of happiness"},{"time":267000,"text":"is that happiness and unhappiness"},{"time":269000,"text":"are not endpoints of a single continuum."},{"time":272000,"text":"The Freudian model is really one continuum"},{"time":275000,"text":"that, as you get less miserable,"},{"time":277000,"text":"you get happier."},{"time":279000,"text":"And that isn't true -- when you get less miserable,"},{"time":281000,"text":"you get less miserable."},{"time":283000,"text":"And that happiness is a whole other end of the equation."},{"time":286000,"text":"And it's been missing. It's been missing from psychotherapy."},{"time":289000,"text":"So when people's symptoms go away, they tend to recur,"},{"time":292000,"text":"because there isn't a sense of the other half --"},{"time":294000,"text":"of what pleasure, happiness, compassion, gratitude,"},{"time":297000,"text":"what are the positive emotions."},{"time":299000,"text":"And of course we know this intuitively,"},{"time":301000,"text":"that happiness is not just the absence of misery."},{"time":304000,"text":"But somehow it was not put forward until very recently,"},{"time":307000,"text":"seeing these as two parallel systems."},{"time":310000,"text":"So that the body can both look for opportunity"},{"time":313000,"text":"and also protect itself from danger, at the same time."},{"time":315000,"text":"And they're sort of two reciprocal"},{"time":317000,"text":"and dynamically interacting systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"People have also wanted to deconstruct."},{"time":321000,"text":"We use this word \"happy,\""},{"time":323000,"text":"and it's this very large umbrella of a term."},{"time":325000,"text":"And then three emotions for which there are no English words:"},{"time":328000,"text":"fiero, which is the pride in accomplishment of a challenge;"},{"time":332000,"text":"schadenfreude, which is happiness in another's misfortune,"},{"time":336000,"text":"a malicious pleasure;"},{"time":338000,"text":"and naches, which is a pride and joy in one's children."},{"time":341000,"text":"Absent from this list, and absent from any discussions of happiness,"},{"time":344000,"text":"are happiness in another's happiness."},{"time":346000,"text":"We don't seem to have a word for that."},{"time":349000,"text":"We are very sensitive to the negative,"},{"time":351000,"text":"but it is in part offset by the fact"},{"time":353000,"text":"that we have a positivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"We're also born pleasure-seekers."},{"time":357000,"text":"Babies love the taste of sweet"},{"time":359000,"text":"and hate the taste of bitter."},{"time":361000,"text":"They love to touch smooth surfaces rather than rough ones."},{"time":364000,"text":"They like to look at beautiful faces"},{"time":366000,"text":"rather than plain faces."},{"time":368000,"text":"They like to listen to consonant melodies"},{"time":370000,"text":"instead of dissonant melodies."},{"time":372000,"text":"Babies really are born"},{"time":374000,"text":"with a lot of innate pleasures."},{"time":376000,"text":"There was once a statement made by a psychologist"},{"time":379000,"text":"that said that 80 percent of the pursuit of happiness"},{"time":382000,"text":"is really just about the genes,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and it's as difficult to become happier as it is to become taller."},{"time":387000,"text":"That's nonsense."},{"time":389000,"text":"There is a decent contribution to happiness from the genes --"},{"time":392000,"text":"about 50 percent --"},{"time":394000,"text":"but there is still that 50 percent that is unaccounted for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"Let's just go into the brain for a moment,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and see where does happiness"},{"time":401000,"text":"arise from in evolution."},{"time":403000,"text":"We have basically at least two systems here,"},{"time":406000,"text":"and they both are very ancient."},{"time":408000,"text":"One is the reward system,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and that's fed by the chemical dopamine."},{"time":412000,"text":"And it starts in the ventral tegmental area."},{"time":415000,"text":"It goes to the nucleus accumbens,"},{"time":417000,"text":"all the way up to the prefrontal cortex, orbital frontal cortex,"},{"time":419000,"text":"where decisions are made, high level."},{"time":421000,"text":"This was originally seen as a system"},{"time":423000,"text":"that was the pleasure system of the brain."},{"time":425000,"text":"In the 1950s,"},{"time":427000,"text":"Olds and Milner put electrodes into the brain of a rat."},{"time":430000,"text":"And the rat would just keep pressing that bar"},{"time":433000,"text":"thousands and thousands and thousands of times."},{"time":435000,"text":"It wouldn't eat. It wouldn't sleep. It wouldn't have sex."},{"time":438000,"text":"It wouldn't do anything but press this bar."},{"time":440000,"text":"So they assumed"},{"time":442000,"text":"this must be, you know, the brain's orgasmatron."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"It turned out that it wasn't,"},{"time":446000,"text":"that it really is a system of motivation,"},{"time":448000,"text":"a system of wanting."},{"time":450000,"text":"It gives objects what's called incentive salience."},{"time":453000,"text":"It makes something look so attractive"},{"time":455000,"text":"that you just have to go after it."},{"time":457000,"text":"That's something different"},{"time":459000,"text":"from the system that is the pleasure system,"},{"time":462000,"text":"which simply says, \"I like this.\""},{"time":464000,"text":"The pleasure system, as you see,"},{"time":466000,"text":"which is the internal opiates, there is a hormone oxytocin,"},{"time":469000,"text":"is widely spread throughout the brain."},{"time":471000,"text":"Dopamine system, the wanting system,"},{"time":473000,"text":"is much more centralized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"The other thing about positive emotions is that they have a universal signal."},{"time":478000,"text":"And we see here the smile."},{"time":480000,"text":"And the universal signal is not just raising the corner of the lips"},{"time":483000,"text":"to the zygomatic major."},{"time":485000,"text":"It's also crinkling the outer corner of the eye,"},{"time":488000,"text":"the orbicularis oculi."},{"time":491000,"text":"So you see, even 10-month-old babies, when they see their mother,"},{"time":494000,"text":"will show this particular kind of smile."},{"time":496000,"text":"Extroverts use it more than introverts."},{"time":498000,"text":"People who are relieved of depression"},{"time":500000,"text":"show it more after than before."},{"time":502000,"text":"So if you want to unmask a true look of happiness,"},{"time":505000,"text":"you will look for this expression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"Our pleasures are really ancient."},{"time":509000,"text":"And we learn, of course, many, many pleasures,"},{"time":511000,"text":"but many of them are base. And one of them, of course, is biophilia --"},{"time":514000,"text":"that we have a response to the natural world"},{"time":516000,"text":"that's very profound."},{"time":518000,"text":"Very interesting studies"},{"time":520000,"text":"done on people recovering from surgery,"},{"time":523000,"text":"who found that people who faced a brick wall"},{"time":526000,"text":"versus people who looked out on trees and nature,"},{"time":529000,"text":"the people who looked out on the brick wall"},{"time":531000,"text":"were in the hospital longer, needed more medication,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and had more medical complications."},{"time":535000,"text":"There is something very restorative about nature,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and it's part of how we are tuned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"Humans, particularly so, we're very imitative creatures."},{"time":543000,"text":"And we imitate from almost the second we are born."},{"time":545000,"text":"Here is a three-week-old baby."},{"time":547000,"text":"And if you stick your tongue out at this baby,"},{"time":549000,"text":"the baby will do the same."},{"time":551000,"text":"We are social beings from the beginning."},{"time":553000,"text":"And even studies of cooperation"},{"time":555000,"text":"show that cooperation between individuals"},{"time":557000,"text":"lights up reward centers of the brain."},{"time":560000,"text":"One problem that psychology has had"},{"time":562000,"text":"is instead of looking at this intersubjectivity --"},{"time":564000,"text":"or the importance of the social brain"},{"time":567000,"text":"to humans who come into the world helpless"},{"time":569000,"text":"and need each other tremendously --"},{"time":571000,"text":"is that they focus instead on the self"},{"time":574000,"text":"and self-esteem, and not self-other."},{"time":576000,"text":"It's sort of \"me,\" not \"we.\""},{"time":578000,"text":"And I think this has been a really tremendous problem"},{"time":580000,"text":"that goes against our biology and nature,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and hasn't made us any happier at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"Because when you think about it, people are happiest when in flow,"},{"time":588000,"text":"when they're absorbed in something out in the world,"},{"time":590000,"text":"when they're with other people, when they're active,"},{"time":592000,"text":"engaged in sports, focusing on a loved one,"},{"time":594000,"text":"learning, having sex, whatever."},{"time":596000,"text":"They're not sitting in front of the mirror"},{"time":598000,"text":"trying to figure themselves out,"},{"time":600000,"text":"or thinking about themselves."},{"time":602000,"text":"These are not the periods when you feel happiest."},{"time":605000,"text":"The other thing is, that a piece of evidence is,"},{"time":607000,"text":"is if you look at computerized text analysis"},{"time":610000,"text":"of people who commit suicide,"},{"time":612000,"text":"what you find there, and it's quite interesting,"},{"time":614000,"text":"is use of the first person singular --"},{"time":616000,"text":"\"I,\" \"me,\" \"my,\""},{"time":618000,"text":"not \"we\" and \"us\" --"},{"time":620000,"text":"and the letters are less hopeless"},{"time":622000,"text":"than they are really alone."},{"time":624000,"text":"And being alone is very unnatural to the human."},{"time":628000,"text":"There is a profound need to belong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"But there are ways in which our evolutionary history can really trip us up."},{"time":634000,"text":"Because, for example, the genes don't care whether we're happy,"},{"time":637000,"text":"they care that we replicate,"},{"time":639000,"text":"that we pass our genes on."},{"time":641000,"text":"So for example we have three systems"},{"time":643000,"text":"that underlie reproduction, because it's so important."},{"time":646000,"text":"There's lust, which is just wanting to have sex."},{"time":649000,"text":"And that's really mediated by the sex hormones."},{"time":652000,"text":"Romantic attraction,"},{"time":654000,"text":"that gets into the desire system."},{"time":656000,"text":"And that's dopamine-fed. And that's, \"I must have this one person.\""},{"time":659000,"text":"There's attachment, which is oxytocin,"},{"time":661000,"text":"and the opiates, which says, \"This is a long-term bond.\""},{"time":664000,"text":"See the problem is that, as humans, these three can separate."},{"time":667000,"text":"So a person can be in a long term attachment,"},{"time":670000,"text":"become romantically infatuated with someone else,"},{"time":672000,"text":"and want to have sex with a third person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"The other way in which our genes can sometimes lead us astray"},{"time":677000,"text":"is in social status."},{"time":679000,"text":"We are very acutely aware of our social status"},{"time":682000,"text":"and always seek to further and increase it."},{"time":686000,"text":"Now in the animal world, there is only one way to increase status,"},{"time":689000,"text":"and that's dominance."},{"time":691000,"text":"I seize command by physical prowess,"},{"time":693000,"text":"and I keep it by beating my chest,"},{"time":695000,"text":"and you make submissive gestures."},{"time":697000,"text":"Now, the human has a whole other way to rise to the top,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and that is a prestige route,"},{"time":702000,"text":"which is freely conferred."},{"time":704000,"text":"Someone has expertise and knowledge, and knows how to do things,"},{"time":707000,"text":"and we give that person status."},{"time":709000,"text":"And that's clearly the way for us to create many more niches of status"},{"time":713000,"text":"so that people don't have to be lower on the status hierarchy"},{"time":716000,"text":"as they are in the animal world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"The data isn't terribly supportive of money buying happiness."},{"time":721000,"text":"But it's not irrelevant."},{"time":723000,"text":"So if you look at questions like this, life satisfaction,"},{"time":726000,"text":"you see life satisfaction going up with each rung of income."},{"time":729000,"text":"You see mental distress going up with lower income."},{"time":733000,"text":"So clearly there is some effect."},{"time":735000,"text":"But the effect is relatively small."},{"time":737000,"text":"And one of the problems with money is materialism."},{"time":740000,"text":"What happens when people pursue money too avidly,"},{"time":743000,"text":"is they forget about the real basic pleasures of life."},{"time":746000,"text":"So we have here, this couple."},{"time":748000,"text":"\"Do you think the less-fortunate are having better sex?\""},{"time":750000,"text":"And then this kid over here is saying, \"Leave me alone with my toys.\""},{"time":752000,"text":"So one of the things is that it really takes over."},{"time":755000,"text":"That whole dopamine-wanting system"},{"time":757000,"text":"takes over and derails from any of the pleasure system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"Maslow had this idea back in the 1950s"},{"time":762000,"text":"that as people rise above their biological needs,"},{"time":765000,"text":"as the world becomes safer"},{"time":767000,"text":"and we don't have to worry about basic needs being met --"},{"time":770000,"text":"our biological system, whatever motivates us, is being satisfied --"},{"time":774000,"text":"we can rise above them, to think beyond ourselves"},{"time":777000,"text":"toward self-actualization or transcendence,"},{"time":780000,"text":"and rise above the materialist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"So to just quickly conclude with some brief data"},{"time":785000,"text":"that suggests this might be so."},{"time":788000,"text":"One is people who underwent what is called a quantum change:"},{"time":791000,"text":"they felt their life and their whole values had changed."},{"time":794000,"text":"And sure enough, if you look at the kinds of values that come in,"},{"time":797000,"text":"you see wealth, adventure, achievement, pleasure, fun, be respected,"},{"time":800000,"text":"before the change,"},{"time":802000,"text":"and much more post-materialist values after."},{"time":806000,"text":"Women had a whole different set of value shifts."},{"time":809000,"text":"But very similarly, the only one that survived there was happiness."},{"time":812000,"text":"They went from attractiveness and happiness and wealth and self-control"},{"time":815000,"text":"to generosity and forgiveness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818000,"text":"I end with a few quotes."},{"time":820000,"text":"\"There is only one question:"},{"time":822000,"text":"How to love this world?\""},{"time":824000,"text":"And Rilke, \"If your daily life seems poor,"},{"time":827000,"text":"do not blame it; blame yourself."},{"time":829000,"text":"Tell yourself that you are not poet enough"},{"time":831000,"text":"to call forth its riches.\""},{"time":834000,"text":"\"First, say to yourself what you would be."},{"time":836000,"text":"Then do what you have to do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":838000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":840000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}